{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# SVD"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%matplotlib inline\n",
    "\n",
    "from PIL import Image\n",
    "import imageio\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from sklearn.datasets import load_boston"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Using SVD to compress images"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def plot(X):\n",
    "    plt.imshow(X, cmap='gray', vmin=0, vmax=255)\n",
    "    plt.axis('off')\n",
    "    \n",
    "def size(u, s, v):\n",
    "    return u.shape[0] * u.shape[1] + s.shape[0] + v.shape[0] * v.shape[1]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "img = Image.open('img/flud.jpg')\n",
    "img.load()\n",
    "X = np.asarray(img, dtype=\"int32\")\n",
    "X = X.mean(axis=2)\n",
    "plot(X)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "First, let's use all singular values."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "U shape - (503, 503)\n",
      "S shape - (503,)\n",
      "V shape - (800, 800)\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "U, S, V = np.linalg.svd(X)\n",
    "print('U shape - {0}\\nS shape - {1}\\nV shape - {2}'.format(U.shape, S.shape, V.shape))\n",
    "plot((U * S).dot(V[:len(S)]))\n",
    "plt.title('Compression rate with all singular values - {0:.02%}'.format(\n",
    "    1 - size(U, S, V[:len(S)]) / size(U, S, V)))\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Let's try to use only top singular values thus compressing image even more."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "images = []\n",
    "for i in range(10, 110, 10):\n",
    "    u = U[:,:i]\n",
    "    s = S[:i]\n",
    "    v = V[:i]\n",
    "    plot((u * s).dot(v))\n",
    "    plt.title('Using {0} singular values, compression rate = {1:.02%}'.format(\n",
    "        i, 1 - size(u, s, v) / size(U, S, V)))\n",
    "    plt.savefig('img/svd/{0}.jpg'.format(i))\n",
    "    images.append(imageio.imread('img/svd/{0}.jpg'.format(i)))\n",
    "    plt.close()\n",
    "\n",
    "imageio.mimsave('img/svd_demo.gif', images, duration=1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "![SVD demo](img/svd_demo.gif)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Note, that first singular values capture most of information."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 747,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plt.plot(S)\n",
    "plt.title('Singular values')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# SVD for linear regression\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\hat \\beta = (X^T X)^{-1} X^T y = V S^{-1} U^T y$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 748,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "X = load_boston().data\n",
    "y = load_boston().target\n",
    "# add ones to dataset \n",
    "X = np.hstack([np.ones(506)[:, np.newaxis], X])\n",
    "# calculate beta using direct inverse\n",
    "beta = np.linalg.inv(X.T.dot(X)).dot(X.T).dot(y)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Calculate beta using direct inverse"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 749,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "RMSE = 21.894831181729206\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "beta = np.linalg.inv(X.T.dot(X)).dot(X.T).dot(y)\n",
    "print('RMSE = {0}'.format(np.mean((X.dot(beta) - y)**2)))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Calculate using SVD"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 750,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "RMSE = 21.894831181729206\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "U, S, V = np.linalg.svd(X)\n",
    "S = np.hstack([np.diag(S), np.zeros((14, 492))]).T    # X ~ U.dot(S).dot(V)\n",
    "beta_svd = V.T.dot(np.linalg.pinv(S)).dot(U.T).dot(y)\n",
    "print('RMSE = {0}'.format(np.mean((X.dot(beta_svd) - y)**2)))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Note:** sklearn and most other libraries use SVD for regression."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Recommender using SVD"
   ]
  },

   "outputs": [],
   "source": [

    "## MovieLense dataset\n",
    "\n",
    "You can download dataset from here: https://grouplens.org/datasets/movielens/latest/"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 770,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "ratings = pd.read_csv('ml-latest-small/ratings.csv')\n",
    "movies = pd.read_csv('ml-latest-small/movies.csv', index_col=0)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Limit to top movies so that we don't run out of memory\n",
    "n_movies = 1000\n",
    "movie_idx_map = {v: i for i, v in enumerate(ratings.groupby('movieId').size().sort_values().tail(n_movies).index)}\n",
    "ratings = ratings[ratings.movieId.isin(movie_idx_map)]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create matrix\n",
    "X = np.zeros((n_users, n_movies))\n",
    "for u, m, r, _ in ratings.values:\n",
    "    X[int(u) - 1, movie_idx_map[int(m)]] = r"
   ]
  },
